This week on the Major Issues Podcast, the hosts celebrate Christmas Day with Merry Little Batman, the animated holiday tale that puts the spotlight on a young Damian Wayne left alone in Wayne Manor on the most dangerous night of the year. As Gotham’s rogues close in, Damian suits up to prove he can be Batman—whether his father believes it or not.

The hosts break down how the film balances heartfelt holiday spirit with classic Batman chaos, explore Damian’s obsession with legacy and heroism, and discuss why this surprisingly emotional Christmas story stands out among DC’s animated offerings. It’s festive, funny, and full of bat-shaped heart. 🎄🦇

 

